        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 6:52PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 652 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Little Neck to Forest Hills to Brooklyn
Heights. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Jamaica and Flatbush around 700 PM EDT.
Lynbrook and Woodmere around 705 PM EDT.
Baldwin and Cedarhurst around 710 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
